               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Haymanotä ʾabaw “Faith of the Fathers” (fols. 1ra-151rc)
 II)
                     Maṣḥafa ṭomār “Book of the Letter (from Heaven)” (fols. 151rc-153vb)
 -
                     Table of contents (fols. 153vc, 154va-154vc)
 
 Colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1ra" to="154vc"/>
                     <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5769HaymanTomar">Hāymānota ʾabaw with Maṣḥafa ṭomār</title>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="1ra" to="151rc"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1586Hayman">Hāymānota ʾabaw</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="151rc" to="153vb"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1978Mashaf">Maṣḥafa ṭomār</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                        <locus from="153vc" to="154vc"/>
                        <title ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1586Hayman#Contents">No item: LIT1586Hayman, could not check for Contents</title>
                     </msItem>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#153vb">153vb</locus>: በአኰቴተ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ ተጽሕፈ፡ ሃይማኖተ፡ አበው፡ ቅዱሳን፡
                        በመዋዕለ፡ ንጉሥነ፡ መፍቀሬ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ [vac] ዘተጸውዓ፡ በጸጋ፡ ጥምቀት፡ በከመ፡ ሰማዕት፡ [vac] በረድኤተ፡
                        ቅዱስ፡ [vac] ወበአስተሐምሞታ፡ ለነዳይት፡ [vac] ወተፈጸመ፡ እምአመ፡ ነግሠ፡ በ፳ወ፰ዓመት፡ በዘመነ፡ ዮሐንስ፡
                        ወንጌላዊ፡ ወአሜሃ፡ ኮነ፡ ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ፸፻ወ፩፻፶ወ፪፡ ባሕቱ፡ ፈጣሬ፡ ዓለማት፡ ያኑኅ፡ መዋዕሊሁ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ ዳግማይ፡
                        ቈስጠንጢኖስ፡ ዘሐደሳ፡ ለብልየተ፡ ዓለም፡ በርትዕት፡ ሃይማኖት፡ ወይዕቀቦ፡ ከመ፡ ብንተ፡ ዓይን፡ &lt;…&gt; <foreign xml:lang="en">By the glory of God, the faith of the
                        righteous fathers was written during the reign of our king lover of God [vac]
                        who was named by the grace of baptism, according to witnesses, ... by the help
                        of St ... and by the care of poor .... It was completed on the 28th year from
                        the time he became king, during the year of John the evangelist. At that time
                        the year of mercy was 7152. Moreover the creator of the world may prolong the
                        age of our king Constantine II, who renewed the oldness of the world with the
                        Orthodox faith. May He protect him like the pupil.</foreign> 
                        <note>Given and baptismal names of
                        the king, and other names are skipped in the colophon. </note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
