               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0165DSM">Dabra Sāhl Qǝddus Mikāʾel Bet Maḵāʿ</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate when="1660">Ca. 1660 (?). The colophon indicates
                        that the Ms. was completed on the year of mercy 7152 (=1660 A.D.) which
                        falls upon the time of King Fāsiladas (r. 1632-67). It mentions the 28th
                        year of reign of a king was is “Dāgǝmāwi Qʷasṭanṭinos” ("the second
                        Constantine"). King Fāsiladas’ regnal name was ʿālam Sagad; Both hand a and
                        hand b seem to be of a later time.</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>The name of a possible donor, Maḫtama
                     Krǝstos, is inserted between the punctuation signs on <locus target="#153vb">153vb</locus>.</provenance>
               </history>
